> Rclone mount is run through nssm service
 
[NSSM](https://nssm.cc) - non sucking service manager

NSSM is desided as a root level command line point

The nssm code that I use is 

> mount --allow-other --dir-cache-time 1h --drive-chunk-size 256M --log-file=rclone_Mount_log_YYY_MM_DD.txt --log-level DEBUG --buffer-size 512M--vfs-read-chunk-size 64M --vfs-read-chunk-size-limit off Google_Crypt: M: --config "C:\Users\Matt\.rclone.conf" 


This is run via a Python Windows script
